abstract: The ABC late night host outdrew his two older competitors, David Letterman and Jay Leno, among the younger viewers prized by advertisers, though his show lagged slightly in overall audience numbers.
snippet: The ABC late night host outdrew his two older competitors, David Letterman and Jay Leno, among the younger viewers prized by advertisers, though his show lagged slightly in overall audience numbers.
lead_paragraph: On his third day as an 11:35 p.m. late night host, Jimmy Kimmel took his biggest step yet to separate himself from the two titans of that time period, David Letterman and Jay Leno. He started pulling away, at least for one night, among the most important audience in late night.

headline.main: Kimmel Gains in Coveted 18-49 Age Group
